ci_np <- read_excel(here("data", "ci_np.xlsx"))

#Making the first ggplot graph Visualizing visitors to Channel Islands National Park

gg_base <- ggplot(data = ci_np,
      aes(x = year, y = visitors))

gg_base +
  geom_line()

gg_base +
  geom_point()

gg_base +
  geom_col()

gg_base +
  geom_area()

We can also start customizing ggplot graphs

gg_base +
  geom_line(
    color = "purple",
    linetype = "dashed"
  )

gg_base +
  geom_point(
    color = "purple",
    pch = 17,
    size = 4,
    alpha = 0.5
  )

gg_base +
  geom_area(
    color = "green",
    fill = "green",
    alpha = 0.5
  )

## mapping variables onto aesthetics
gg_base +
  geom_point(
    aes(size = visitors,
        color = visitors),
    alpha = 0.5
  )

gg_base +
  geom_col(aes(fill = visitors))
